        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28949",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No there is not.\n\nAs you note: \n$filename = dirname(_FILE_) . '\/Data\/' .$locale . '.xml'\n\ndirname is the directory where Data.php resists.\nSubdir Data and the file ca.xml.\n\nYou way that the file is there, and Zend_Locale says that it can not read the file.\n\nMaybe both is true.\nStill, this is no problem is Zend_Locale but a file system, privilege or php settings problem.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-19T10:00:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-19T10:00:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28950",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What I wanted to say it, that when it works on one server but not on the second simply check the settings.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-19T10:09:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-19T10:09:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28956",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jcerdan",
                        "name": "jcerdan",
                        "displayName": "Jordi Cerdan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Okay, stupid me, I have disabled temporarily safe_mode and now the script is running fine. \n\nSo the problem is the function file_exists() with safe_mode activated.\n\nEven if I have\nsafe_mode_include_dir = .:\/usr\/local\/php5\/lib\/php\n\nI get this error.\n\nSo I did:\ncd \/usr\/local\/php5\/lib\/php\/Zend\/Locale\nchown -R www-data Data\n\nAnd that solved the problem.\n\nThanks for your help, I think you can mark this as solved and may be this detail about safe mode (even it'll be removed in PHP 6) should be mentionned in the install instructions.\n\nKind regards.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jcerdan",
                        "name": "jcerdan",
                        "displayName": "Jordi Cerdan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-19T11:09:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-19T11:09:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28958",
